cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.GR

This paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning for solving games and tasks in robotics, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The specific task being addressed is the Ball-in-Maze game, which involves navigating a ball through a maze, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of trajectories to improve sample efficiency, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) if the trajectories are generated from visual input, or graphics (cs.GR) if the trajectories are generated from a simulator. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.RO, followed by cs.CV and cs.GR.
